n reduced sympathetic inflow to the heart, seemingly via an inhibition of norepinephrine release from sympathetic nerves. VNS' sympatholytic/vagotonic action dilated cardiac microcirculatory vessels and improved left ventricular contractility in patients with severe CAD. Copyright © 2001 Elsevier Science B.V.},
   author = {A. V. Zamotrinsky and B. Kondratiev and J. W. De Jong},
   doi = {10.1016/S1566-0702(01)00227-2},
   issn = {15660702},
